results.title: How can I clean the rubber sides of my mouse? - Microsoft Q&A
results.description: Better answers are either: remove this inferior coating material with a strong solvent, like Goop-off or you can sand off the coating with sandpaper as shown on the youtube video. clean the surface then apply a clear lacquer or varnish. If you disassemble the mouse and/or mask it properly, you can use a "fixative" often sold in art.
